of one American family.</i>

03:01.909 --> 03:06.174
New York, 1985.

03:24.219 --> 03:25.131
Download.

03:29.810 --> 03:30.782
Get up!

03:31.016 --> 03:32.793
I'm cookin', I'm cookin'...

03:32.960 --> 03:33.965
I'm on the roll.

03:34.133 --> 03:36.512
What's the matter with you?

03:36.713 --> 03:37.517
Boom!

03:41.773 --> 03:42.879
Where is dad?

03:43.046 --> 03:45.057
I don't know, office maybe...

03:46.866 --> 03:49.882
- Whitley!
- Oh, now I have you.

03:50.016 --> 03:51.692
I got you! Got you, baby!

03:51.960 --> 03:54.305
What's the problem, the computer or you?

03:54.909 --> 03:58.360
Today it was everything, I tell you.
It was full scale revolution, total war.

03:58.393 --> 03:59.566
Give me your jacket.

03:59.902 --> 04:02.985
Terrible day.
What a day, what a day, what a schmear.

04:03.420 --> 04:05.229
Hey hey, what's the matter?
Give me a kiss!

04:05.296 --> 04:06.771
There is something wrong with you?

04:09.719 --> 04:10.993
I had such a terrible day.

04:11.026 --> 04:13.205
First the computer turns off,

04:13.305 --> 04:16.408
then the wolf painting jumps off the wall.

04:16.742 --> 04:19.043
It attacks me without provocation.

04:19.077 --> 04:21.846
Then your mother calls, the toilet explodes.

04:21.913 --> 04:24.882
The duck I'm cooking tries to tell me
how to live my life.

04:25.049 --> 04:28.385
The computer completely erased itself
when it turned off.

04:28.418 --> 04:32.656
No wonder that I can't write my great
American novel.

04:33.990 --> 04:37.694
Does this mean you're too tired
to go to the country?

04:38.227 --> 04:40.263
No, it doesn't mean that.

04:41.530 --> 04:43.099
What did you lose?

04:43.399 --> 04:45.167
I lost... you know, I lost another day,

04:45.201 --> 04:48.804
what I lost was gold,
golden notions erased, smoked dreams,

04:48.837 --> 04:51.306
phantoms...
What I crave is... you know

04:51.941 --> 04:53.342
...consolation.

04:57.746 --> 04:58.914
Oh, brother...

05:00.148 --> 05:03.351
You know, it could be the computer
turned off for a reason.

05:04.752 --> 05:05.953
Why would that be?

05:06.354 --> 05:07.455
It could be...

05:09.757 --> 05:12.026
I felt that the book I'm...

05:12.260 --> 05:14.061
working on is no good.

05:14.195 --> 05:16.230
What? Why you do that to yourself?

05:16.797 --> 05:18.499
It was a rotten accident.

05:22.969 --> 05:25.572
- Once the duck...
- We'll get to go down the fire escape?

05:25.771 --> 05:28.106
Not again...
This one is bad.

05:28.240 --> 05:29.541
- Give me something.
- Here, here.

05:29.708 --> 05:31.777
- Just give me something.
- You're gonna need some water.

05:31.910 --> 05:34.245
Give me... something to put on it.

05:35.313 --> 05:36.748
I need to turn it off.

05:37.382 --> 05:41.353
What the code is?
664... 6664...?

05:41.653 --> 05:43.954
- It's 18-57
- Don't... don't... don't...! Please!

05:44.055 --> 05:46.056
The year we were married.

05:46.289 --> 05:49.058
Don't... The red light is on!
Oh no...

05:49.225 --> 05:50.960
Remember what happened last time.

05:50.994 --> 05:52.695
Oh God... will you get the door?

05:54.463 --> 05:56.331
I'm sorry, we get...
we get the little...

05:56.698 --> 05:59.299
- ...small catastrophe.
- Geez. Are you ok?

05:59.533 --> 06:00.501
Honey...

06:00.967 --> 06:02.335
What's the matter?

06:03.469 --> 06:05.537
What isn't the matter,
will you look at this?

06:06.405 --> 06:08.073
Open the window.

06:08.340 --> 06:09.441
Give me that.

06:10.341 --> 06:11.876
Get some air in here.

06:12.777 --> 06:14.545
Could you save me? I married this.

06:15.345 --> 06:17.413
Open the window over there, please!

06:17.446 --> 06:19.048
- Put it over your face.
- Thank you.

06:19.081 --> 06:20.249
Breath shallowly.

06:20.282 --> 06:21.850
We are not going to the country,
right?

06:21.883 --> 06:25.820
No, we're going to the country. No problem.
This is all part of the plan...

06:26.888 --> 06:28.120
I know, the last time...

06:28.221 --> 06:29.822
- That's it, heh?
- That's it.

06:29.889 --> 06:30.689
Hi, Al.

06:30.755 --> 06:33.824
- That's the fire?
- It's just food. Food.

06:35.226 --> 06:36.360
The duck.

06:36.627 --> 06:37.528
Really?

06:38.995 --> 06:40.630
That worked to burn the duck.

06:40.797 --> 06:43.566
891 Feetstreet...

06:43.966 --> 06:47.769
- It shouldn't happen...
- ...23, repeat, is a 23.

06:48.869 --> 06:51.705
- You've been warned before.
- I know. I'm sorry.

06:51.805 --> 06:54.140
You'll receive your summons
in the mail.

06:54.274 --> 06:56.542
- This stuff is so sensitive...
- 200 dollars.

06:56.643 --> 06:58.310
No, stop!

06:58.410 --> 06:59.645
New policy.

07:00.145 --> 07:02.347
It just goes off, I don't know what happened...
Thank you.

07:02.380 --> 07:04.115
- Back to the station!
- Thank you!

07:06.416 --> 07:08.451
Let your wife cook.

07:51.550 --> 07:54.552
Dad, turn this thing off!

08:00.524 --> 08:02.592
Turn it off, Dad.

08:05.160 --> 08:08.896
3-9-27-81,
I know what it is.

08:09.863 --> 08:13.500
It's a geometric, not arithmetical.

08:13.966 --> 08:16.569
- It's your birthday? You just repress it.
- It also does not work.

08:17.169 --> 08:18.737
You've never had that alarm here before.

08:18.904 --> 08:22.707
Ah, you see? You see?
Anne knows how to make it work.

08:23.341 --> 08:25.342
Just read the instruction.

08:46.924 --> 08:48.192
Dad...?

08:49.660 --> 08:50.627
Dad?

08:54.864 --> 08:55.731
Dad!

08:57.933 --> 08:58.600
Dad!

08:58.766 --> 09:00.734
- What's up?
- Spider!

09:00.902 --> 09:01.535
What?!

09:01.835 --> 09:02.603
Aaah!

09:04.237 --> 09:05.705
Go on, kill it!

09:05.806 --> 09:06.939
Kill it!

09:07.940 --> 09:10.409
- Oh, that is a big one.
- Here it is, here it is.

09:12.377 --> 09:14.478
Now it's in your pants!

09:15.379 --> 09:17.081
Alex, do something!

09:18.415 --> 09:21.484
Now it's on you!

09:21.617 --> 09:23.652
Just a peaceful night in the country.

09:23.685 --> 09:25.821
There it going to sleep now, with you.

09:25.887 --> 09:27.421
Will sing to you.

09:27.589 --> 09:31.858
If you leave the room and you come
right back in, usually it's gone.

09:33.660 --> 09:34.761
I'm glad...

09:35.194 --> 09:38.031
that this is not my room.

09:40.300 --> 09:41.868
Have a nice night.

09:43.803 --> 09:44.771
You know...

09:45.639 --> 09:49.243
...it might not have been...
a spider I saw.

09:55.550 --> 09:57.352
Say something dirty.

09:57.385 --> 09:58.753
- Socks.
- Come on...

09:58.786 --> 10:01.489
Say... say erect...
Can you say: erection?

10:01.657 --> 10:02.891
I'll never say it!

10:07.329 --> 10:09.766
What do you think he's doing?
Alex?

10:09.799 --> 10:10.766
What do you mean
what I think he's doing?

10:10.800 --> 10:11.567
I know what he's doing.

10:11.601 --> 10:13.937
He's doing the old Romanian turn on,
he's saying:

10:14.104 --> 10:15.738
I see ghosts of wolves.

10:15.906 --> 10:21.245
I see ghosts of wolves that "huuum".
You know I see the dark beautiful forests...

10:21.278 --> 10:23.280
And she's like this...
She's like this.

10:25.449 --> 10:28.252
And at night there would be
only silence.

10:29.020 --> 10:30.955
And I shall hear the wolves.

10:33.358 --> 10:35.093
But there are no wolves here.

10:40.265 --> 10:42.634
I wonder if there are ghosts.

10:44.136 --> 10:45.975
The house is new.

10:46.208 --> 10:48.849
No, I mean the ghosts of the wolves.

10:50.253 --> 10:52.359
The ones that have been killed.

10:58.377 --> 10:59.413
Stop it.

11:00.817 --> 11:02.823
No, quiet, quiet...

11:07.703 --> 11:09.676
So, you wanna fool around?

11:10.077 --> 11:11.749
- You look good.
- Thanks.

11:12.284 --> 11:14.356
It's been an ice age,
I've missed you...

11:14.390 --> 11:16.997
...you old ball and chain.

12:52.203 --> 12:53.540
Is that someone there?

14:58.364 --> 14:59.601
Hey, hey, wow...

14:59.768 --> 15:01.406
What's the matter, boss?
What's the matter?

15:01.573 --> 15:03.578
- There was something here!
- Shake it up, come on.

15:03.746 --> 15:04.582
Something very bad!

15:04.749 --> 15:06.889
Wow, it was the nightmare.
What are you talking about?

15:07.056 --> 15:08.660
No, no dad.

15:13.341 --> 15:15.948
- It was the nightmare.
- They had me, dad.

15:16.115 --> 15:18.456
Nightmares do that.
You know, sometimes, I mean...

15:18.622 --> 15:23.670
If it didn't do that, that wouldn't be
a nightmare... You know what I mean?

15:23.737 --> 15:26.311
Daddies... daddies get the boys back, right?

15:26.612 --> 15:27.581
Yeah...

15:27.648 --> 15:29.320
Do you know any songs?

15:30.624 --> 15:32.930
Do you know any Indian hunting songs?

15:35.705 --> 15:37.911
Do you know the old buffalo hunting song?

15:49.844 --> 15:53.555
...and cocktails for two.

15:55.929 --> 15:57.533
That's a good boy.
Go to sleep.

15:58.569 --> 16:01.444
He was yelling, you didn't hear him,
he was yelling.

16:01.645 --> 16:04.387
- You were yelling? Where was I?
- He had some bad dream, I tell you.

16:04.554 --> 16:06.359
I had a bad dream too.

16:08.365 --> 16:11.072
I was so sound asleep...
I... I was asleep.

16:11.239 --> 16:13.847
You were out. Like a log.

16:15.719 --> 16:19.664
He said something was after him, some spider, huh?
Like a spider from last night?

16:20.198 --> 16:22.304
It was real, dad.

16:23.641 --> 16:25.280
Worst dream you ever had.

16:25.581 --> 16:27.519
It wasn't a dream.

16:29.091 --> 16:31.063
I'm not surprised about you, Whit.

16:31.431 --> 16:35.141
You ate your way through this...
table last night.

16:35.309 --> 16:37.314
I didn't think he could get up the stairs.

16:37.716 --> 16:39.287
That's a good thing it was nothing.
No wonder...

16:39.321 --> 16:43.433
I pay fortune for this equipment.
Some animal must have set it off.

16:44.569 --> 16:45.572
How did you sleep?

16:47.577 --> 16:48.213
Well...

16:48.513 --> 16:50.821
We saw lots of lights last night.

16:52.356 --> 16:54.530
Whitley has that machine finely tuned.

16:55.867 --> 16:57.205
A mosquito could set it off.

16:57.271 --> 16:59.678
No, really there were lots of lights,
it was very hard to sleep.

16:59.845 --> 17:01.349
A chipmunk couldn't set that thing off.

17:01.517 --> 17:03.589
It's been the light from the bathroom.

17:03.756 --> 17:06.297
No, it was light there came in
from outside.

17:06.364 --> 17:09.339
I can't believe you didn't see it,
it was like day.

17:09.507 --> 17:11.713
I thought there was a fire outside,
in fact.

17:11.880 --> 17:15.892
I came downstairs, you know...
there was light... it was this light.

17:16.460 --> 17:18.766
But then... it must...

17:21.205 --> 17:24.819
The flood lights went on, I don't know...
it was the moon maybe.

17:26.159 --> 17:28.573
We were all dreaming,
you know, and the moon...

17:28.673 --> 17:30.673
we all got involved in the same dream.

17:32.343 --> 17:34.416
It wasn't the moon.

17:34.852 --> 17:36.889
So it was a dream.

17:37.058 --> 17:40.099
This whole place was flooded
with light from above.

17:40.266 --> 17:42.104
It wasn't a dream.

17:42.237 --> 17:43.508
So it was the moon.

17:44.043 --> 17:45.681
No, it wasn't the moon.

17:46.048 --> 17:48.856
And it wasn't a dream.
I'm telling you what we saw.

17:57.413 --> 17:58.249
Well...

18:02.026 --> 18:07.171
So, why don't you have your usual huge
portion of... banana cakes?

18:09.350 --> 18:11.494
Aromatic compounds...

18:14.824 --> 18:17.463
- Don't do this to me.
- Aromatic compounds of perfumes.

18:17.760 --> 18:20.728
- No, no, no!
- 1,2,3,4,5,6.

18:20.893 --> 18:22.641
OK. I want to go home.

18:23.399 --> 18:26.467
I'm sorry, I'm not angry.
I can't explain.

18:27.489 --> 18:29.402
Whitley, I want you to take us back today.

18:29.666 --> 18:31.842
Come on, Alex.
Give me a break.

18:32.337 --> 18:34.151
I know I did not see the moon.

18:34.678 --> 18:35.965
I want to go home.

18:36.558 --> 18:39.197
Alex, what's the four letter word,
for an odour...

18:39.362 --> 18:41.340
Take us home, Whitley!

18:44.671 --> 18:46.123
Please, forgive me.

18:46.815 --> 18:47.969
It's cool.

18:49.426 --> 18:51.834
Would you... clean up, then we'll go.

18:51.998 --> 18:54.010
We had a really rough night.

18:54.175 --> 18:56.351
- Are you kidding?
- What's going on?

19:06.080 --> 19:08.587
I don't know why we're doing this.
Why...

19:10.894 --> 19:12.445
It's crazy. You know.

19:16.699 --> 19:18.381
Thank you for taking us home.

19:19.634 --> 19:20.660
It's fine.

19:21.207 --> 19:23.601
We could have taken the bus, Whitley.
Really.

19:23.841 --> 19:25.550
There is no bus.

19:26.269 --> 19:28.299
There is not even a bus station.

20:00.898 --> 20:03.398
This is gonna be so terrible.

20:04.498 --> 20:06.998
Another day down the toilet.

20:07.098 --> 20:11.098
What are you doing, Whitley?

20:11.198 --> 20:12.698
Is your video on?

20:12.798 --> 20:15.798
Are you wasting time again, you devil?

20:22.898 --> 20:24.398
Anybody seen Andy?

20:50.398 --> 20:51.898
What's going on?

20:51.998 --> 20:53.498
Had a good time?

20:54.298 --> 20:55.798
It was okay.

20:57.398 --> 20:59.398
Did someone say something to you?

20:59.498 --> 21:00.498
No.

21:00.598 --> 21:01.597
Get you into a fight?

21:01.697 --> 21:02.697
No.

21:02.797 --> 21:04.297
Is that Andy in there?

21:04.397 --> 21:05.897
Oh yeah.

21:06.497 --> 21:08.997
Thought I was talking to a pirate.

21:09.897 --> 21:11.397
Everyone like your teeth?

21:14.997 --> 21:17.497
I don't like the space ship anymore.

21:17.597 --> 21:19.097
It's ugly.

21:20.249 --> 21:25.008
There were wolves in the closet, wolves
in the basement, wolves all over the place.

21:26.373 --> 21:29.735
They work in advertising, they sell
junk food and beer.

21:30.135 --> 21:33.663
They eat gigantic hamburgers,
and they drink cold beers,

21:33.829 --> 21:37.491
for the baseball games on the TV,
and the bags of the potato chips,

21:37.657 --> 21:40.519
which are big enough to feed a horse.

21:41.218 --> 21:42.450
They have a lot of fun.

21:42.616 --> 21:44.414
There go the baseball games.
They have a hack of

21:44.580 --> 21:45.711
Get dressed!

21:45.878 --> 21:47.675
I don't feel like it, go with someone else.

21:47.709 --> 21:49.539
I'm old. I'll probably get hurt.

21:50.072 --> 21:53.067
Come on, come on! We've got ten minutes
to be over at Greenberg's. Andy's waiting.

21:53.367 --> 21:57.128
Crack the whip.
Drive the slaves off to another cocktail party.

21:57.627 --> 22:01.455
Make them babble about Glasnost.
I've lost another day here.

22:01.621 --> 22:04.054
He needs you.
He's over sensitive today.

22:04.120 --> 22:05.386
He's in a funny mood.

22:05.953 --> 22:06.952
What's the matter?

22:07.120 --> 22:08.353
I don't know. He...

22:08.519 --> 22:11.752
He overreacted this morning at school.
He won't talk to me, I'm a girl.

22:11.918 --> 22:13.585
Here, put this on...

22:14.585 --> 22:16.218
take this off...

22:17.518 --> 22:20.017
You're going as an elephant.
You promised him.

22:22.350 --> 22:23.917
Is this the front...?

22:24.517 --> 22:26.050
-... or the rear?
- I don't know.

22:27.182 --> 22:30.282
Will you put your grey turtleneck on.
Elephants are grey.

22:31.349 --> 22:33.782
- Put your pants on, come on, let's go.
- It's me!

22:34.114 --> 22:35.015
Come on.

22:44.479 --> 22:46.846
OK, OK, it's just about that time.

22:48.846 --> 22:50.579
The queen is speaking...

22:53.412 --> 22:57.211
OK! Remember! Only treats, no tricks.

22:57.378 --> 22:58.411
Yeah!

22:59.844 --> 23:04.110
Get your bags to the door!
God help the rest of the building.

23:15.273 --> 23:17.540
Come on, Dad. You can come with me.

23:22.072 --> 23:24.039
- Bye bye!
- Bye!

23:26.038 --> 23:27.872
Don't let anybody step on you.

23:29.971 --> 23:32.404
- Thanks a lot, Jake. Sorry about the mess.
- You're welcome.

23:32.571 --> 23:33.970
You can take off the nose.

23:34.137 --> 23:37.336
What's the matter, you don't like my nose?
How come I can't have any fun?

23:37.836 --> 23:40.236
The other dads have noses.

23:40.436 --> 23:41.903
- Put this on ice.
- OK.

23:42.735 --> 23:44.302
You can use this, it's clean.

23:44.335 --> 23:45.269
Take care, guys...

23:45.335 --> 23:46.468
- See you later.
- All right.

23:46.634 --> 23:47.768
Come on! Let's go to work!

23:47.934 --> 23:49.967
- You're sure you've not blown this?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

23:50.801 --> 23:53.001
Bye guys, see you later!

23:53.734 --> 23:56.400
Don't be afraid.
I'm starting to get scared.

23:57.966 --> 23:59.699
I'm starting to get scared now...

24:01.432 --> 24:02.599
Which way in there?

24:08.830 --> 24:11.196
I think we're expected to go down there.

24:16.829 --> 24:17.795
Zoom...

24:59.988 --> 25:01.521
Trick or treat...?

25:06.987 --> 25:08.020
Get away!

25:08.620 --> 25:10.553
What... what you... what you...!

25:11.585 --> 25:12.485
Stay away from me!

25:12.651 --> 25:13.785
No more!

25:14.484 --> 25:16.217
- Are you crazy?
- What's going on?

25:16.384 --> 25:17.584
What's that suppose to mean?

25:17.651 --> 25:19.550
It's the Halloween show.

25:21.550 --> 25:23.616
What's the matter with you?
A grown man getting hysterical

25:23.716 --> 25:25.216
over a thirteen year old
girl in a Halloween costume.

25:25.282 --> 25:26.216
I'm sorry, I'm sorry...

25:26.382 --> 25:27.682
Please, leave us alone.

25:38.114 --> 25:40.013
Am I in the dog house or what?

25:44.979 --> 25:46.712
Andy, say good night to a father.

25:51.211 --> 25:55.111
I'm gonna put our son to bed
and then we're going to talk.

25:55.411 --> 25:57.877
- Oh, wonderful.
- No, it won't be wonderful.

25:58.410 --> 25:59.643
But it's needed.

26:03.076 --> 26:04.676
That guy went crazy.

26:07.142 --> 26:08.542
Not my fault.

26:13.473 --> 26:14.359
Here we go.

26:16.436 --> 26:17.867
How old are you?

26:18.241 --> 26:20.046
I overreacted.

26:20.625 --> 26:22.601
What's going on Whitley?
What's happening?

26:23.725 --> 26:25.462
- What's happen to you...
- I got scared.

26:27.300 --> 26:28.905
What do you take me for?

26:29.339 --> 26:31.445
What do you think,
I don't know what you do?

26:33.985 --> 26:35.856
You're having problems with your writing?

26:36.024 --> 26:38.230
So fine,
you terrified our son tonight.

26:38.397 --> 26:40.536
I scared myself too.

26:41.372 --> 26:43.176
You were frightened
by a Halloween mask.

26:43.343 --> 26:44.579
Mhm. Yes.

26:45.248 --> 26:47.220
A Halloween mask frightened you.

26:48.322 --> 26:49.559
