54:58.209 --> 55:00.647
It's a simple process.

55:00.814 --> 55:04.379
It's sometimes very helpful in cases
of psychological trauma,

55:04.463 --> 55:07.470
when people have difficulty remembering
what happened to them.

55:07.970 --> 55:09.970
Well, you think about that, and...

55:10.070 --> 55:12.870
If you decide to do it
you can give me a call.

55:12.970 --> 55:13.970
Thank you.

55:14.811 --> 55:17.224
I'd stick pins in my eyeballs before I'd let
that...

55:17.324 --> 55:20.124
that wacko woman fool with me.

55:20.407 --> 55:21.925
This woman is a pro.

55:22.912 --> 55:25.457
Sam sent you to her,
her evidence is accepted in court.

55:26.539 --> 55:28.075
Did you listen to her?

55:30.395 --> 55:31.691
What do you mean I did listen to her?

55:31.864 --> 55:33.849
Why should I pay someone to talk to me?

55:34.059 --> 55:35.760
Because you fired God damned gun
at me last week!

55:35.944 --> 55:37.571
I'm all right with seeing her!

55:37.080 --> 55:38.761
She should pay me!

55:38.943 --> 55:42.707
Selfish prick.
Sit up and talk to me!

55:43.166 --> 55:44.775
I'd rather be dead.

55:45.433 --> 55:46.894
I'm gonna tell you something:

55:48.611 --> 55:52.302
You gonna go back in that woman's office,
we gonna find out what's wrong with you...

55:52.375 --> 55:54.348
or we're not gonna have any marriage left.

55:57.783 --> 55:59.384
I'm sitting up! I'm sitting.

55:59.551 --> 56:00.518
My shoes hurt.

56:01.685 --> 56:03.821
I'm sitting. So, you know, lighten up.

56:07.489 --> 56:08.890
Crazy women...

56:09.891 --> 56:11.559
So, what do I do?

56:11.625 --> 56:13.560
What should I do?
Where would you like me to go?

56:13.726 --> 56:15.995
It's best he'd be alone
his first time.

56:16.661 --> 56:17.362
Alright.

56:25.500 --> 56:26.600
So?

56:27.201 --> 56:29.069
It's not exactly the electric chair.

56:31.937 --> 56:34.472
Listen to me Whitley.
Look up at my finger.

56:35.473 --> 56:38.242
That's it. Keep looking at my finger.

56:40.243 --> 56:43.578
I'm going to count to ten,
as you're falling asleep.

56:44.312 --> 56:47.981
And when I'm finished, you'll be
deeply, deeply asleep.

56:49.082 --> 56:51.183
One... falling asleep,

56:52.417 --> 56:55.419
two... falling asleep,

56:56.587 --> 56:59.721
thee... falling asleep,

57:00.756 --> 57:03.758
four... falling asleep,

57:06.859 --> 57:09.962
five... falling asleep,

57:11.829 --> 57:12.897
Whitley?

57:15.666 --> 57:22.170
Whitley, let's go back to that first time,
the night of October 4th.

57:22.403 --> 57:24.404
Last October 4th

57:24.570 --> 57:25.871
What do you see?

57:26.904 --> 57:28.473
October 4th...

57:30.941 --> 57:37.588
Busy day. Writing, cooking,
mess in the kitchen and...

57:37.823 --> 57:40.261
Alex and Sara came. Going to the country.

57:41.331 --> 57:42.433
Yes?

57:42.600 --> 57:46.441
So we're in a car, we're talking, and there's
a lot of traffic, and it's getting dark...

57:46.642 --> 57:50.718
We get up there and I can't get
the security system to work. It's...

57:50.885 --> 57:53.124
just every time I touch it, it goes crazy.

57:53.725 --> 57:56.264
Anne fixes it, we go in the house...

57:56.632 --> 58:00.540
build a fire.
First fire in the season.

58:01.776 --> 58:02.978
And we went to bed.

58:03.146 --> 58:05.050
What happens after you go to bed?

58:05.818 --> 58:08.157
I wake up, middle of the night.

58:12.734 --> 58:15.841
That's...
I don't... I don't...

58:24.460 --> 58:26.598
Something went past my window.

58:31.941 --> 58:34.613
- Something went past the window?
- A light.

58:37.820 --> 58:39.924
Big, like a light.

58:41.795 --> 58:42.797
But...

58:43.332 --> 58:45.770
I don't want to think about that, so...

58:47.273 --> 58:48.809
I go back to sleep.

59:05.779 --> 59:07.382
Is that someone there?

59:07.850 --> 59:08.685
You know...

59:09.286 --> 59:10.589
I see you.

59:11.691 --> 59:13.195
I'm seeing some...

59:13.361 --> 59:14.831
I'm seeing someone there...

59:14.998 --> 59:16.534
I don't think I like this.

59:17.671 --> 59:18.873
- It's going fine.
- Get out!

59:19.106 --> 59:20.276
It's going fine...

59:21.311 --> 59:22.280
Away!

59:23.316 --> 59:26.222
Get away!
Out! Get out!

59:26.856 --> 59:27.891
Get away!

59:30.096 --> 59:32.300
Why me? What have I done?

59:36.610 --> 59:38.713
This is no god. I can't do this.

59:39.716 --> 59:41.720
Whitley, tell me what you see.

59:42.020 --> 59:44.993
It's almost as if this figure is...

59:47.699 --> 59:51.741
It's covered in something,
it's sticking something into my mind.

59:54.314 --> 59:56.625
Images exploding...

59:59.595 --> 01:00:01.110
The world is blowing up...

01:00:06.632 --> 01:00:08.256
My boy is dead.

01:00:10.927 --> 01:00:14.139
Why I have to die, dad?
Why?

01:00:20.280 --> 01:00:22.915
I'm not hypnotized now?
Am I?

01:00:23.275 --> 01:00:25.513
I think you just came out of it.

01:00:29.513 --> 01:00:31.013
I can't do this.

01:00:31.613 --> 01:00:33.112
What did I see?

01:00:33.212 --> 01:00:34.798
I don't know.

01:00:34.898 --> 01:00:37.415
I want to go home now.
I can't do this.

01:00:38.506 --> 01:00:41.547
I don't need this. Bad dreams.

01:00:46.163 --> 01:00:47.138
Whitley?

01:00:48.906 --> 01:00:50.674
It was a bad state.

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:52.227
But it's over.

01:00:53.310 --> 01:00:55.367
It'll never be over, not now.

01:00:55.547 --> 01:00:58.435
Whatever happened is in the past,
and you're fine.

01:00:58.795 --> 01:01:00.528
You don't know, you said it.

01:01:01.286 --> 01:01:03.289
That's true, but it's all right.

01:01:03.956 --> 01:01:04.758
Whitley...

01:01:08.130 --> 01:01:10.501
Let him go, let him work this out.

01:01:41.581 --> 01:01:43.180
Excuse me, I'm lost.

01:01:43.613 --> 01:01:46.944
Can you help me? Do you know if this
bus goes to the end of the line?

01:01:53.208 --> 01:01:54.540
You know...

01:01:57.539 --> 01:01:58.871
I can't believe this.

01:02:01.503 --> 01:02:02.935
It's an ambush.

01:02:04.901 --> 01:02:06.900
You, people... you're in...

01:02:07.000 --> 01:02:11.797
I'm telling, you're in for one big surprise.
One very big surprise.

01:02:21.625 --> 01:02:24.124
- You want anything else, Whit?
- No, thank you.

01:02:28.821 --> 01:02:31.438
- They're all looking for you.
- How did you know?

01:02:31.606 --> 01:02:33.182
Anne said to look here.

01:02:33.485 --> 01:02:34.927
Women know everything.

01:02:35.095 --> 01:02:36.403
Let's go home.

01:02:38.113 --> 01:02:39.523
They tell you what happened?

01:02:40.663 --> 01:02:41.703
A little.

01:02:42.207 --> 01:02:46.031
When the doctor hypnotized me, I was
supposed recall prowlers, or something...

01:02:46.099 --> 01:02:49.758
but in fact I recall something else...
I sure do.

01:02:49.959 --> 01:02:51.098
What?

01:02:51.601 --> 01:02:54.077
Little blue fuckers,
about that big.

01:02:54.177 --> 01:02:57.577
When I was a boy we knew of these things.

01:02:59.177 --> 01:03:01.677
In the mountains
there were many mines.

01:03:03.577 --> 01:03:05.077
Strange men were seen.

01:03:05.377 --> 01:03:07.377
Little and tough.

01:03:08.077 --> 01:03:10.477
They were called gobbles.

01:03:10.577 --> 01:03:12.577
The people of the lower depth.

01:03:13.877 --> 01:03:14.877
Gobbles?

01:03:16.577 --> 01:03:18.577
You're talking about munchkins?

01:03:19.977 --> 01:03:21.977
You're talking about trolls?

01:03:22.077 --> 01:03:23.577
You're talking about... leprechauns?

01:03:23.677 --> 01:03:24.777
What are you talking about?

01:03:24.877 --> 01:03:26.577
Whitley, the little men are evil.

01:03:26.677 --> 01:03:28.177
They have haunted the world forever.

01:03:28.677 --> 01:03:31.177
You're talking about folk... stuff.

01:03:32.577 --> 01:03:33.577
I don't know...

01:03:33.677 --> 01:03:35.677
Trolls, or something.

01:03:35.777 --> 01:03:37.277
I'm talking about something else.

01:03:39.894 --> 01:03:41.961
We're back! I found him!

01:03:43.195 --> 01:03:45.062
- How are you feeling?
- Good.

01:03:48.597 --> 01:03:50.999
I'm sorry that I got so crazy.

01:03:51.165 --> 01:03:52.932
Oh, don't worry about it.

01:03:53.099 --> 01:03:54.500
- I've been thinking...
- Any calls?

01:03:54.667 --> 01:03:55.567
No.

01:03:57.167 --> 01:03:58.568
Whitley...

01:04:00.235 --> 01:04:02.736
There is a group, that meets that...

01:04:02.904 --> 01:04:04.604
you might want to join?

01:04:04.937 --> 01:04:05.971
Group?

01:04:06.205 --> 01:04:08.472
People who've seen the same
sort of things you have.

01:04:09.739 --> 01:04:11.307
No, I don't think so.

01:04:11.806 --> 01:04:13.541
Whitley, they are real.

01:04:13.841 --> 01:04:18.243
I have a dozen patients who've all
reported seeing the same beings you saw.

01:04:20.377 --> 01:04:21.210
No!

01:04:22.678 --> 01:04:23.678
All right.

01:04:24.578 --> 01:04:28.481
There is one illness,
temporal lobe epilepsy.

01:04:29.414 --> 01:04:31.581
It might cause such vivid hallucinations.

01:04:31.748 --> 01:04:35.249
Yes, but we all saw the light.
Do we all have epilepsy?

01:04:35.417 --> 01:04:38.118
Even I heard some strange noises.

01:04:39.351 --> 01:04:43.419
There is a test that you can take
to determine whether you have the disease.

01:04:43.952 --> 01:04:47.087
Oh, this is going to be just
a little bit unpleasant.

01:04:47.621 --> 01:04:49.455
There's sticking... it sticking...

01:04:49.621 --> 01:04:52.189
Don't move.
Stay very still now.

01:04:52.523 --> 01:04:53.423
Don't talk.

01:04:55.056 --> 01:04:56.624
How long does this take?

01:04:56.791 --> 01:04:58.692
Not long, not long.

01:04:58.892 --> 01:05:00.826
About 45 minutes.

01:05:01.026 --> 01:05:04.494
I would like you to do
some deep breathing exercises for me.

01:05:04.560 --> 01:05:07.095
OK, breath in deeply through your mouth.

01:05:12.964 --> 01:05:14.298
Close your eyes.

01:05:16.933 --> 01:05:18.467
Open your eyes.

01:05:21.367 --> 01:05:25.436
Now, that medication I gave you earlier
is gonna make you take a little nap.

01:05:47.744 --> 01:05:49.078
What is it, Whit?

01:05:58.882 --> 01:05:59.749
Good news!

01:06:00.216 --> 01:06:01.883
The test came back negative.

01:06:02.050 --> 01:06:05.484
You do not have temporal lobe epilepsy.

01:06:12.388 --> 01:06:13.421
Hi, dad.

01:06:13.888 --> 01:06:16.556
Dad, I waited and waited for you
to come home.

01:06:18.723 --> 01:06:20.759
Help me get to sleep, daddy?

01:06:22.527 --> 01:06:25.297
I'm having a very hard time
without you.

01:06:27.132 --> 01:06:30.403
<i>Without a sound the white camellia fell,</i>

01:06:31.671 --> 01:06:35.342
<i>To sound the darkness of the deep stone well.</i>

01:06:35.576 --> 01:06:38.612
That's a lot of pictures for a few words.

01:06:39.013 --> 01:06:40.080
Yeah.

01:06:40.615 --> 01:06:43.251
It's a kind of a poem called "Haiku".

01:06:43.685 --> 01:06:46.354
Dad, I have a very bad problem.

01:06:47.255 --> 01:06:50.492
- What's that?
- There's a skull staring at me.

01:06:50.658 --> 01:06:54.029
With huge eyes.
I can see it in my head.

01:06:56.098 --> 01:06:57.500
Do you have a bad dream?

01:06:57.766 --> 01:06:58.767
No.

01:07:03.506 --> 01:07:05.775
I saw little blue doctors, dad.

01:07:05.942 --> 01:07:08.211
And tall thin ones too.

01:07:08.545 --> 01:07:09.980
With big eyes.

01:07:10.147 --> 01:07:12.616
Were they real, dad?

01:07:13.284 --> 01:07:15.019
I don't know.

01:07:16.487 --> 01:07:18.689
What do you think they are?

01:07:18.857 --> 01:07:21.994
I don't know. They kind of scare me.

01:07:22.627 --> 01:07:23.795
Kind of?

01:07:24.196 --> 01:07:26.599
Not totally, they're ugly and...

01:07:27.299 --> 01:07:29.168
that's scary, but...

01:07:30.369 --> 01:07:31.504
inside...

01:07:33.506 --> 01:07:36.176
they are sort of soft and perfect.

01:07:36.544 --> 01:07:37.911
Like that poem.

01:08:40.747 --> 01:08:44.118
Ten... falling asleep.

01:08:44.952 --> 01:08:47.455
Deeply, deeply asleep.

01:08:51.426 --> 01:08:54.629
Anne, let's go back in time.

01:08:55.429 --> 01:08:57.265
Do you remember Christmas?

01:08:58.966 --> 01:09:01.069
All right, let's go back further.

01:09:01.437 --> 01:09:05.742
Go back to the night,
that Alex and Sara came to the house.

01:09:06.609 --> 01:09:08.144
Do you remember that night?

01:09:09.412 --> 01:09:11.448
Well, it wasn't a very peaceful night.

01:09:12.049 --> 01:09:13.015
Go on.

01:09:16.086 --> 01:09:17.622
The house was full.

01:09:19.924 --> 01:09:21.459
It was like a party.

01:09:21.859 --> 01:09:23.060
A party?

01:09:23.662 --> 01:09:26.531
I don't think Whitley was there
right much of the time.

01:09:27.631 --> 01:09:29.131
What about your son.

01:09:29.299 --> 01:09:30.233
God!

01:09:30.700 --> 01:09:32.368
Oh God, he's screaming.

01:09:39.140 --> 01:09:41.008
It's painful to hear.

01:09:41.642 --> 01:09:44.042
Oh, it's like something's
happening to him. It's...

01:09:44.211 --> 01:09:46.279
Whitley is going, I wanna go.

01:09:46.712 --> 01:09:47.912
I've got to go.

01:09:48.981 --> 01:09:50.881
You are not suppose to go.

01:09:52.183 --> 01:09:53.884
I've got to go!

01:09:55.852 --> 01:09:58.120
You are suppose to stay in bed.

01:10:00.388 --> 01:10:04.025
I've got to go, my baby is screaming!

01:10:04.124 --> 01:10:05.392
Anne, who is talking to you?

01:10:05.458 --> 01:10:10.562
I can't say! I'm not suppose to say, I don't know!
I'm not supposed to do this!

01:10:11.130 --> 01:10:13.165
Why? What's preventing you?

01:10:14.732 --> 01:10:16.834
I'm out of it... I'm out of it, right?
I'm out of it.

01:10:17.067 --> 01:10:18.569
Yes, quite suddenly.

01:10:18.669 --> 01:10:21.405
I don't know...
there was somebody, there was something...

01:10:22.905 --> 01:10:24.807
There was somebody else...

01:10:32.746 --> 01:10:36.049
He calls them "little doctors".

01:10:39.651 --> 01:10:41.086
I don't like this.

01:10:42.153 --> 01:10:44.155
He seems so little.

01:10:46.022 --> 01:10:47.224
What should we do?

01:10:48.925 --> 01:10:51.627
Should he be hypnotized,
we send him to Janet?

01:10:53.228 --> 01:10:54.929
No, he is too young.

01:10:57.697 --> 01:11:00.399
I'll go back myself,
see what this is.

01:11:07.004 --> 01:11:13.609
Whitley, let's go back now to the night
of December 26th, the day after Christmas.

01:11:14.210 --> 01:11:15.777
What are you having for supper?

01:11:20.048 --> 01:11:24.718
Goose... and a cranberry sauce, sweet potatoes,
Christmas leftovers.

01:11:27.353 --> 01:11:30.055
Now, go forward to later that night.

01:11:30.489 --> 01:11:32.023
Go forward.

01:11:32.590 --> 01:11:33.958
What happens?

01:11:35.426 --> 01:11:37.160
I'm checking out the house.

01:11:37.527 --> 01:11:38.428
Why?

01:11:40.596 --> 01:11:43.232
In case there might be somebody there...

01:11:43.599 --> 01:11:44.766
...hiding.

01:11:45.233 --> 01:11:46.134
Who?

01:11:46.301 --> 01:11:48.202
Those things people.

01:11:48.536 --> 01:11:51.638
- Did you know about those people then?
- Sure.

01:11:52.605 --> 01:11:54.073
Did you tell anyone?

01:11:55.141 --> 01:11:56.809
Well, I wasn't supposed to.

01:12:00.110 --> 01:12:01.311
I have a gun.

01:12:03.412 --> 01:12:04.981
Why do you have a gun?

01:12:05.781 --> 01:12:06.848
I have that...

01:12:07.249 --> 01:12:09.717
the feeling... that

01:12:11.385 --> 01:12:12.319
there might...

01:12:16.022 --> 01:12:18.457
...be somebody there, hiding.

01:12:20.192 --> 01:12:20.993
In the house.

01:12:21.159 --> 01:12:24.928
I'm going to take you further forward
in that night.

01:12:25.596 --> 01:12:28.565
You relax, deep sleep.

01:12:28.732 --> 01:12:31.200
You're going to remain calm.

01:12:31.968 --> 01:12:32.768
What happens?

01:12:32.935 --> 01:12:36.438
I am you. You are me,
and...

01:12:38.005 --> 01:12:39.539
we are here.

01:12:43.943 --> 01:12:47.179
I am the dreamer, you are the dream.

01:13:01.990 --> 01:13:03.290
Is that someone there?

01:13:45.055 --> 01:13:45.556
Wow!

01:13:49.458 --> 01:13:50.526
Wait a minute.

01:13:53.328 --> 01:13:54.595
What are you doing?

01:13:56.363 --> 01:13:57.898
Please, let me go.

01:14:01.134 --> 01:14:03.035
Awful, terrible.

01:14:03.536 --> 01:14:06.103
- What's terrible?
- What they did to me.

01:15:02.980 --> 01:15:05.415
I had enough, I give up.
I wanna go home.

01:15:15.121 --> 01:15:16.255
Be smart.

01:15:26.163 --> 01:15:27.564
Are you old?

01:15:31.099 --> 01:15:33.768
Please, let me go.

01:15:36.570 --> 01:15:37.738
I can't wake up.

01:15:39.339 --> 01:15:41.142
Here I am! I'm naked.

01:15:41.609 --> 01:15:45.280
I'm naked!
I'm talking to you like you were real.

01:15:46.549 --> 01:15:47.750
Go to hell.

01:15:53.424 --> 01:15:54.491
Terrible.

01:16:03.003 --> 01:16:04.605
Can we talk this over?

01:16:06.273 --> 01:16:08.509
It looks like we're
gonna sing White Christmas.

01:16:14.917 --> 01:16:16.352
You're probing my mind.

01:16:33.507 --> 01:16:34.509
I'll kill you.

01:16:39.614 --> 01:16:41.184
How dare you.

01:16:53.232 --> 01:16:54.401
I'll kill you.

01:17:19.932 --> 01:17:21.433
You've broken my mind.

01:17:50.770 --> 01:17:52.206
I can't get out of this.

01:18:01.584 --> 01:18:02.452
Mom.

01:18:07.158 --> 01:18:08.393
Come on in here!

01:18:12.398 --> 01:18:15.168
Oh, he wants a...
he wants his mommy.

01:18:46.508 --> 01:18:47.542
Mommy!

01:18:55.286 --> 01:18:56.954
I can't get out of this!

01:18:57.621 --> 01:18:59.015
One... waking up.

01:18:59.878 --> 01:19:01.703
Two... waking up.

01:19:02.732 --> 01:19:04.523
I'm seeing things from my whole life.

01:19:05.519 --> 01:19:06.714
What is it, Whit?

01:19:09.733 --> 01:19:11.625
Wow...

01:19:12.919 --> 01:19:14.545
Three... you're awake.

01:19:37.374 --> 01:19:38.138
It's been...

01:19:40.593 --> 01:19:41.496
Thank you.

01:19:42.767 --> 01:19:47.649
Now I know, this thing has been
in my life... my whole life.

01:19:48.819 --> 01:19:49.989
I passed it on.

01:19:52.630 --> 01:19:54.201
Now it's with my son.

01:19:59.317 --> 01:20:00.922
I've seen them before.

01:20:02.828 --> 01:20:04.366
In your childhood apparently.

01:20:04.433 --> 01:20:07.843
No, no, no. Like I'm seeing you,
like I'm seeing this.

01:20:07.877 --> 01:20:11.020
Like I'm seeing everything...
seeing room.

01:20:17.974 --> 01:20:19.043
You say, that...

01:20:20.648 --> 01:20:21.885
there is a group.

01:20:22.487 --> 01:20:24.293
Yes, a special group.

01:20:32.986 --> 01:20:34.457
I don't want to be crazy.

01:20:37.566 --> 01:20:41.110
I'd like to introduce Anne and Whitley.

01:20:41.278 --> 01:20:44.236
Whitley's had some very vivid experiences.

01:20:44.464 --> 01:20:45.504
He's a writer...

01:20:45.601 --> 01:20:48.950
I'm not sure, I'm comfortable
with the writer being here, Janet.

01:20:49.113 --> 01:20:51.583
Yeah, the force will kick me off
if this got out.

01:20:51.681 --> 01:20:54.672
Do the rest of you feel threatened
by his profession?

01:20:54.834 --> 01:20:59.158
Let's face it, the newspapers laugh of us.
We're more like entertainment.

01:21:01.759 --> 01:21:05.042
Not that kind of writer.
I'm make it up. I'm a novelist.

01:21:05.205 --> 01:21:06.863
So, what you're gonna write about us?

01:21:06.993 --> 01:21:08.033
A comic novel?

01:21:08.196 --> 01:21:09.496
Wait a minute,

01:21:09.659 --> 01:21:12.357
Whitley isn't here because he is a writer.

01:21:12.519 --> 01:21:14.633
He's here for the same reasons you are.

01:21:14.795 --> 01:21:17.851
Why don't you tell us something
of what you can remember?

01:21:18.013 --> 01:21:19.672
What I remember?

01:21:22.792 --> 01:21:26.562
It couldn't be what happened, that
what happened, I don't know, I remember...

01:21:28.221 --> 01:21:29.489
monsters.

01:21:32.674 --> 01:21:33.877
They came into my house.

01:21:34.040 --> 01:21:40.054
The short stocky ones in the coveralls
or the slim willowy ones with the big eyes.

01:21:40.217 --> 01:21:41.224
Beg your pardon?

01:21:42.005 --> 01:21:42.818
What?

01:21:43.435 --> 01:21:44.996
Who was involved with you?

01:21:46.329 --> 01:21:47.044
What do you mean?

01:21:47.076 --> 01:21:48.539
Oh come on, let's cut the crap.

01:21:48.832 --> 01:21:50.555
Which group of the aliens abducted you?

01:21:50.718 --> 01:21:54.359
Bob, we are not victims,
we are participants.

01:21:54.618 --> 01:21:58.650
Well, I don't know' about you folks,
but I am very definitely a victim.

01:21:58.812 --> 01:22:01.576
I didn't want what happened to me.
I didn't ask for this.

01:22:01.738 --> 01:22:04.599
Wait a minute. Give the guy chance.
So come on, Whitley,

01:22:04.697 --> 01:22:06.809
which group abducted you?

01:22:07.005 --> 01:22:09.379
- Did you see a ship?
- Ship?

01:22:09.671 --> 01:22:10.418
A Ship.

01:22:12.076 --> 01:22:14.417
This happened in the house,
in the country.

01:22:15.132 --> 01:22:19.717
Oh, do you have circle or a triangle scar
anywhere in your body?

01:22:20.756 --> 01:22:21.471
No.

01:22:21.829 --> 01:22:25.957
Because a lot of us have marks. You know,
I want to get back to this participant thing...

01:22:26.120 --> 01:22:32.087
I didn't want what they did to me.
I didn't want a rectal probe, Laurie.

01:22:33.730 --> 01:22:37.232
It's not funny.
That's why I say victim.

01:22:37.448 --> 01:22:39.458
Nobody wants it, nobody asked for it.

01:22:39.626 --> 01:22:42.942
We have to make this experience work for us.

01:22:43.109 --> 01:22:46.190
Otherwise we'll live the rest
of our lives in fear.

01:22:46.459 --> 01:22:47.698
So we get together.

01:22:48.100 --> 01:22:50.579
- And we talk about it.
- And laugh.

01:22:51.282 --> 01:22:52.254
Sometimes.

01:22:53.560 --> 01:22:57.143
Well, we're all space cadets here.
So what the heck.

01:22:57.546 --> 01:22:59.555
You have to make the best of it.
You know.

01:22:59.723 --> 01:23:03.341
This isn't a joke.
These beings are real.

01:23:03.508 --> 01:23:06.388
Even if we don't know what that means.

01:23:07.695 --> 01:23:10.040
It may sound like a clich, but...

01:23:10.475 --> 01:23:13.121
these visitors do come in gigantic ships

01:23:13.591 --> 01:23:15.533
and they contact a lot of people.

01:23:16.974 --> 01:23:23.840
Then of course, we say it's... ee... thunderstorms
or bad dreams, hallucinations, meteors, whatever, but...

01:23:25.179 --> 01:23:26.485
the joke's on us.

01:23:27.323 --> 01:23:28.897
We are the ones who are hiding.

01:23:29.868 --> 01:23:33.352
They came to me one night in 1959.

01:23:33.654 --> 01:23:35.663
I was lying in bed, reading a book,

01:23:35.831 --> 01:23:40.922
when suddenly a group of little men
in blue uniforms walked in the room.

01:23:41.760 --> 01:23:44.272
Short, three or four feet tall.

01:23:44.440 --> 01:23:47.287
Very round, their faces were...

01:23:48.124 --> 01:23:50.703
Well, I was terrified.

01:23:52.010 --> 01:23:55.360
One of them put his hand on my wrist...

01:23:55.527 --> 01:23:57.570
- And it was...
- Clammy.

01:23:57.872 --> 01:23:59.714
Like the skin of a frog.

01:24:00.283 --> 01:24:04.872
And one of them said: don't worry,
it's not you we're interested in.

01:24:07.552 --> 01:24:09.260
We are interested in...

01:24:09.964 --> 01:24:11.772
the girl child you're carrying.

01:24:11.940 --> 01:24:13.681
Did they let you keep her?

01:24:15.022 --> 01:24:16.987
My daughter is a wonderful woman.

01:24:18.254 --> 01:24:20.919
And now her daughter is involved to.

01:24:22.353 --> 01:24:23.552
How old is she?

01:24:24.851 --> 01:24:26.617
My granddaughter is six.

01:24:26.785 --> 01:24:28.082
Passed it on.

01:24:29.216 --> 01:24:33.348
The only thing to do
is to face it.

01:24:33.681 --> 01:24:37.579
Because otherwise it's just gonna
tear your life to pieces.

01:24:37.646 --> 01:24:40.045
Believe me, I know.

01:24:40.213 --> 01:24:42.744
At least you two have each other.

01:24:43.244 --> 01:24:48.942
My husband did not have the experience,
and he tried to have me committed.

01:24:50.342 --> 01:24:53.241
Now at least he doesn't have me
to worry about anymore.

01:24:53.841 --> 01:24:55.973
I wasn't as lucky as Laurie.

01:24:56.706 --> 01:24:59.105
She still has her daughter and the granddaughter.

01:25:00.505 --> 01:25:02.338
I was 3 months pregnant.

01:25:03.238 --> 01:25:07.703
And my husband and I saw this huge light outside.

01:25:09.036 --> 01:25:10.502
We just went to sleep.

01:25:12.368 --> 01:25:15.367
That next morning I woke up
and I wasn't pregnant anymore.

01:25:15.667 --> 01:25:16.800
Whitley...

01:25:17.866 --> 01:25:20.365
Won't you tell us little more
about what happened to you.

01:25:21.632 --> 01:25:23.431
I think I'd like to go home.

01:25:23.997 --> 01:25:26.563
So, it's my wife and I, you know,
we have a family too,

01:25:26.663 --> 01:25:28.462
and we have to think about this.

01:25:34.327 --> 01:25:35.392
Thank you.

01:25:37.759 --> 01:25:39.191
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:25:41.157 --> 01:25:43.257
- Very much.
- Come back.

01:25:48.688 --> 01:25:50.154
I wish you'd stay.

01:25:51.554 --> 01:25:55.519
I tried hypnosis, I tried this, I tried that,
I tried this, I tried that...

01:25:55.985 --> 01:25:59.385
No, it's not working.
I have to do something for myself.

01:25:59.717 --> 01:26:03.150
You expect things,
you expect answers so quickly.

01:26:03.317 --> 01:26:05.749
We don't even know all the questions yet.

01:26:08.582 --> 01:26:11.314
All right, of course. But...

01:26:11.581 --> 01:26:16.412
if... if... if I was in my right mind,
I would know that too.

01:26:18.545 --> 01:26:22.444
There is nothing matter with your mind,
be patient.

01:26:22.710 --> 01:26:24.343
Take care.

01:26:55.131 --> 01:26:56.297
Look at me.

01:27:00.163 --> 01:27:01.562
Am I not gorgeous?

01:27:01.730 --> 01:27:03.362
What the hell...

01:27:12.359 --> 01:27:15.058
You look like you're dressed for your
First Communion.

01:27:16.524 --> 01:27:18.193
Don't wait up for me, baby.

01:27:21.030 --> 01:27:22.165
What are you doing?

01:27:24.669 --> 01:27:25.937
I shall return.

01:27:27.205 --> 01:27:28.407
Where you're going?

01:27:36.517 --> 01:27:38.153
Going for pack of cigarettes.

01:27:50.870 --> 01:27:52.239
You don't smoke.

01:31:54.196 --> 01:31:55.918
I must be awake.

01:31:57.799 --> 01:31:59.240
Is that what you mean?

01:32:01.883 --> 01:32:03.484
I must be awake.

01:33:17.548 --> 01:33:20.151
I'm gonna do a trick.
Look at this.

01:33:20.311 --> 01:33:22.851
Empty, right?
Show him.

01:33:30.873 --> 01:33:32.545
I should cast a spell.

01:33:34.884 --> 01:33:36.388
This has to cook them.

01:33:36.622 --> 01:33:40.099
Wanna say a few things.
First I'd like to say seasons greetings,

01:33:41.001 --> 01:33:45.146
then I'd like to say, keep your hands
on the table at all the times.

01:33:47.986 --> 01:33:49.023
Boo!

01:33:54.102 --> 01:33:57.144
I wanna go home. Please, let me go.

01:33:57.511 --> 01:33:58.949
Are you old?

01:33:59.718 --> 01:34:01.323
You've broken my mind.

01:34:01.589 --> 01:34:02.926
I'll kill you.

01:34:03.194 --> 01:34:05.032
Can we talk this over?

01:34:07.472 --> 01:34:08.975
I can't wake up!

01:34:09.375 --> 01:34:12.915
I am the dreamer. You are the dream.

01:34:14.751 --> 01:34:15.485
Look.

01:34:16.320 --> 01:34:21.128
The only thing that really matters here
is what I'm about to show you.

01:34:42.061 --> 01:34:43.297
That's not it.

01:34:44.733 --> 01:34:46.335
I didn't come all this way...

01:34:46.836 --> 01:34:48.939
for you to tell me
that that's what it is.

01:34:50.308 --> 01:34:53.479
Is there something under that?
Because I don't believe that one.

01:34:57.352 --> 01:34:58.587
It's like a...

01:34:59.088 --> 01:35:01.325
box. A Chinese box.

01:35:02.961 --> 01:35:05.967
You open it and there is another one inside,
and there is another one inside...

01:35:06.233 --> 01:35:08.703
You're not gonna let me see you, are you?

01:35:09.137 --> 01:35:11.341
It is a Chinese box.

01:35:12.443 --> 01:35:15.615
And you're not...
gonna be allowed to see.

01:35:16.917 --> 01:35:20.522
OK? So, just get that clear.

01:35:21.858 --> 01:35:25.030
You're not gonna let us see you.

01:35:25.564 --> 01:35:27.200
That's a good idea.

01:35:59.651 --> 01:36:01.388
One... two, three, shoot!

01:36:05.594 --> 01:36:06.730
Anybody home?

01:36:07.263 --> 01:36:09.000
Dad! Dad!

01:36:11.938 --> 01:36:14.442
What are you doing up?
Why aren't you in school?

01:36:14.608 --> 01:36:17.380
Mom needed me to help her wait for you.

01:36:21.587 --> 01:36:23.056
We are playing war.

01:36:23.523 --> 01:36:27.262
I'm beating the pants off her.
That for sure.

01:36:27.863 --> 01:36:29.700
- I saw them.
- You did?

01:36:30.835 --> 01:36:31.703
Something happened.

01:36:31.770 --> 01:36:32.938
- How are you?
- Good.

01:36:33.005 --> 01:36:35.075
Dad, come here,
I wanna show you something,

01:36:35.142 --> 01:36:37.746
I made a computer game on your computer.

01:36:48.164 --> 01:36:49.231
What happened?

01:36:50.634 --> 01:36:51.769
They danced.

01:36:51.936 --> 01:36:53.205
What kind of dance?

01:36:55.876 --> 01:36:57.578
The bossa nova, how do I know?

01:37:02.251 --> 01:37:04.489
They let me know that I...

01:37:06.359 --> 01:37:07.360
was...

01:37:08.462 --> 01:37:09.664
chosen...

01:37:11.934 --> 01:37:13.136
for something.

01:37:13.470 --> 01:37:14.304
And...

01:37:15.974 --> 01:37:18.311
they invited me to come with them.

01:37:21.616 --> 01:37:23.319
I had the feeling, forever.

01:37:27.292 --> 01:37:28.695
Then it was morning.

01:37:40.546 --> 01:37:42.971
- They asked you to go away with them?
- Yeah.

01:37:44.997 --> 01:37:47.090
I just came home to get my stuff.

01:37:50.346 --> 01:37:52.638
You don't have a mark
on the back of your head.

01:37:54.033 --> 01:37:55.793
I can give you that one.

01:38:14.028 --> 01:38:18.181
You need a theory, you know, it's just
not strange enough, to account for...

01:38:19.675 --> 01:38:21.270
for the facts.

01:38:21.602 --> 01:38:24.094
If we're talking about
what they know about us,

01:38:24.326 --> 01:38:26.685
you'd have to... you would have to consider
that they...

01:38:27.914 --> 01:38:31.070
they could be sitting at home tonight
watching "The Honeymooners".

01:38:31.768 --> 01:38:33.860
Like Ralph and Alice... like us.

01:38:34.027 --> 01:38:35.687
That's why they picked on me.

01:38:36.684 --> 01:38:38.311
You know what I think?

01:38:38.876 --> 01:38:40.458
I don't think it matters.

01:38:42.980 --> 01:38:47.218
Whatever it is,
they know what's the way of television...

01:38:47.387 --> 01:38:48.968
and thing like that.

01:38:51.895 --> 01:38:54.687
If... if we're talking about light years..

01:38:54.855 --> 01:38:57.983
tonight they're watching the first episode
"The Father Knows Best".

01:38:58.723 --> 01:39:01.683
It would be narcissistic of us
to feel alone in the universe.

01:39:01.750 --> 01:39:05.046
People used to think that the world
was flat, you know, the centre of things.

01:39:05.113 --> 01:39:07.805
That excludes the possibility of visitors.

01:39:07.973 --> 01:39:12.038
That's really another kind of...
of the same kind thinking.

01:39:13.657 --> 01:39:18.781
The world is getting so small, that
it would be nice to meet someone new.

01:39:20.500 --> 01:39:22.482
I don't know, I don't know, I don't know...

01:39:24.102 --> 01:39:25.623
I don't know what you saw.

01:39:28.035 --> 01:39:30.051
What is it matter?
It doesn't matter.

01:39:30.745 --> 01:39:32.187
It's just God.

01:39:33.730 --> 01:39:37.620
You saw something extraordinary?
There are many faces of God.

01:39:39.464 --> 01:39:41.275
Masks of God.

01:39:42.952 --> 01:39:45.266
Our history is a response to their presence.

01:39:45.433 --> 01:39:50.865
They might be what the face of evolution
looks like on the response to...

01:39:51.737 --> 01:39:53.683
a conscious mind.

01:39:54.823 --> 01:39:56.198
You know something?

01:40:00.624 --> 01:40:02.154
It frightened me.

01:40:03.616 --> 01:40:05.844
Because you went so far away...

01:40:10.932 --> 01:40:12.262
but you're back...

01:40:14.190 --> 01:40:15.620
you're different.

01:40:18.213 --> 01:40:20.242
I think they gave you something.

01:40:23.501 --> 01:40:26.360
I do. I think they gave you a gift.

01:40:29.785 --> 01:40:31.304
You'd better use it.

01:40:34.104 --> 01:40:36.104
Look what I've got for you.

01:40:36.204 --> 01:40:38.204
Mandarin pressed duck.

01:40:38.304 --> 01:40:40.804
A beautiful bottle of Bordeaux.

01:40:40.904 --> 01:40:43.204
I'm gonna drop that book,
you know, that I'm writing.

01:40:43.304 --> 01:40:44.304
Oh yeah?

01:40:44.404 --> 01:40:46.104
What are you gonna do?
Drive a cab?

01:40:46.204 --> 01:40:47.704
I'm gonna write about this.

01:40:49.104 --> 01:40:50.104
Us.

01:40:50.704 --> 01:40:52.704
I'm gonna write about what I know.

01:40:54.804 --> 01:40:56.204
I like that look in your eyes.

01:40:56.304 --> 01:40:57.804
I'm gonna do it right now.

01:40:59.104 --> 01:41:00.804
Watch this.

01:41:10.803 --> 01:41:12.303
Watch out!

01:41:12.403 --> 01:41:13.903
Whitley is back!

01:41:18.706 --> 01:41:20.299
You're sleeping?

01:41:23.584 --> 01:41:26.438
Like this:
I gotta know, I gotta know what is...

01:41:26.698 --> 01:41:29.393
Look at this, Anne, wake up, wake up.

01:41:29.559 --> 01:41:31.056
I got this great.

01:41:31.223 --> 01:41:33.884
It's the first chapter, look, look, awake.

01:41:38.110 --> 01:41:39.242
OK, OK.

01:41:40.539 --> 01:41:45.097
I've got this great first chapter.
I got such an idea. About how to start.

01:42:17.104 --> 01:42:19.366
Andy... Andy wake up.

01:42:19.532 --> 01:42:21.728
Come on, come on.
Wake up.

01:42:22.029 --> 01:42:23.359
I'll show you something.

01:42:30.280 --> 01:42:31.744
Whitley...

01:42:51.374 --> 01:42:53.183
What's going on?

01:42:55.761 --> 01:42:58.340
- What are we doing?
- It was a huge light.

01:42:58.373 --> 01:42:59.981
Are we searching for something?

01:43:02.892 --> 01:43:04.366
What are we doing?

01:43:05.773 --> 01:43:07.447
Mom, what are we doing?

01:43:07.882 --> 01:43:09.289
Nothing.

01:43:09.457 --> 01:43:11.402
Let's go back to bed.

01:43:13.248 --> 01:43:15.655
You think it could have been a plane?
Helicopter?

01:43:20.107 --> 01:43:23.075
- So beautiful. You see the moon?
- Let's go back.

01:43:30.066 --> 01:43:32.867
Andy, wait, wait... come here.
Come here...

01:44:00.406 --> 01:44:04.431
Maybe we do have an afterlife,
but not quite in the way...

01:44:04.538 --> 01:44:06.601
tradition suggests.

01:44:06.735 --> 01:44:11.301
Maybe you and I are larvae,
and the "visitors"...

01:44:11.435 --> 01:44:14.450
are human beings in the mature form.

01:44:14.552 --> 01:44:18.913
Certainly, we are consuming
our planet's resources...

01:44:24.592 --> 01:44:30.425
But in state, I'm sure in transform...

01:44:31.009 --> 01:44:33.889
astronomers of India believed...

01:44:39.831 --> 01:44:41.946
Why call a book...

01:44:44.206 --> 01:44:46.904
...about you?

